title: Star Wars Build-a-Bears
body:
For the last couple of years, Build-a-Bear has been rolling out new Star Wars friends and accessories at a pretty consistent rate.

Build-a-Bear offers multiple bears that are inspired by Star Wars characters. Each has a starting price of $35.

Kylo Ren Bear - starting at $35

Chewbacca - starting at $35

Captain Phasma Bear - starting at $35

Stormtrooper Bear - starting at $35

Rey Bear - starting at $35

Additionally, Build-a-Bear also offers a basic bear patterned with Star Wars icons. 

Dark Side vs Light Side Bear - starting at $30

question: silent fury
answer:
Kesterren

He kept his eyes downcast, always. 

Not because he believed them when they told him that he was inferior. And not because he agreed that aliens (like him) were nothing but lesser versions of the Sith purebloods and humans who sneered at him, and spat their hatred when he passed by them in the foreboding halls of the Academy. He belonged here. Nothing that they said or did could make him feel ashamed of who he was, or what he was learning to become.

No, he kept them lowered because he understood that a predator’s best advantage was the element of surprise. He kept his eyes lowered in a pretense of humility, of deference… so that no one would see the silent fury seething in the golden depths until it was far too late for them to escape.
